President Obama and his wife, Michelle, express their sadness over the passing of Roger Ebert. They highlight his influence on a generation of Americans and Chicagoans, considering him the embodiment of the movies. The President acknowledges Ebert's honesty in his film reviews and his ability to capture the magical essence of cinema. Despite battling cancer, Ebert remained productive and continued to share his passion and perspective. The President concludes by stating that the movies will not be the same without him and offers thoughts and prayers to Ebert's wife, Chaz, and the rest of his family.